/-!
# Jacobi theta functions

Define Jacobi theta functions Θ₂, Θ₃, Θ₄ and their fourth powers H₂, H₃, H₄.
Prove that H₂, H₃, H₄ are modualar forms of weight 2 and level Γ(2).
Also Jacobi identity: Θ₂^4 + Θ₄^4 = Θ₃^4.
-/

